    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e6ac523-7122-4994-9f51-7ca67065222a",
      "key": "6694d1a0-d05e-4315-b2f0-e4e8f2d189f8",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "365fd365-6ec4-4fbb-9434-1df366aa77f8",
      "key": "44714196-9d08-4a8a-bec0-40f0fd53febd",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Itinerary"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Ch3\u003EDay 1\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EWe meet at our designated pick up points and transfer by private coach to our allocated London airport for our direct scheduled Turkish Airlines flight to Istanbul. On arrival at Istanbul we are met by our guide who will accompany us on all transfers and included day excursions. We transfer in our private executive coach to the 4* Barcelo Hotel in Istanbul for a four night stay. A welcome dinner is included at our hotel this evening.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDay 2\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EThis morning we meet our guide for a tour of the old city. We start by heading to the Sultanahmet district in the heart of historic Old Istanbul and our first visit is to the Blue Mosque. The masterwork of the 17th century Ottoman architect Sedefk\u00E2r Mehmet Aga, with its six minarets and a great cascade of domes, the Mosque is a great feature of the Istanbul skyline. We continue to Topkapi Palace. Home of the Ottoman sultans for nearly 400 years and the heart of the vast Ottoman Empire, Topkapi is today a museum of the old Turkish way of life. During our visit to Topkapi Palace, we see the Fruit Room of Ahmet II, adorned with fruit and floral paintings. This afternoon we visit the Byzantine Church of Hagia Sophia, among the finest architectural works in the world. Its wide, flat dome was a daring engineering feat in the 6th century and architects still marvel at the building\u0026#39;s many innovations. Our day concludes with a visit to the Underground Cistern which was built in the 6th century and supplied water throughout the city during the Byzantine and Ottoman times. Re-discovered in 1545, it was used to water the gardens of Topkapi Palace.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDay 3\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EDolmabah\u00E7e Palace is our destination this morning, built by Sultan Abd\u00FCl Mecit in 1856. The extravagant opulence of the palace belies the fact that it was built at a time when the Ottoman Empire was in decline. We then enjoy an included fish lunch. This afternoon we embark on an included cruise on the Bosphorus. We board the boat at Sariyer, a charming fishing village where the Bosphorus meets the Black Sea, and enjoy a perfect vantage point to see the Sultan\u2019s palaces, Rumeli Fortress, the mansions and modern villas forming the elegant part of the city.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDay 4\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EThis morning we visit the Church of St Saviour in Chora, dating back to the 11th century and home to a fine selection of Byzantine mosaics and frescoes. We continue to the S\u00FCleymaniye Mosque. One of the grandest and most beautiful of the Ottoman mosques, it crowns one of Istanbul\u0026#39;s seven hills and dominates the Golden Horn providing a landmark for the entire city. Our guide then accompanies us to the Grand Bazaar of Istanbul. With 60 alleyways and 3,000 shops, it is the oldest and largest in the world. The bazaar was established by Mehmet II shortly after his conquest of the city in 1453. Our day concludes with a visit to the Spice Bazaar. The bazaar came to specialise in spices from the Orient, taking advantage of Istanbul\u2019s site on the trade route between the East (where most spices are grown) and Europe.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDay 5\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EAfter spending the morning at leisure in Istanbul, we return to Istanbul Airport for our direct scheduled Turkish Airlines back to our allocated London airport. We then continue by private coach back to our original pick up points.\u003C/p\u003E\n"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "34e5aa3b-db10-40a1-893d-79e98cd3f2f4",
